  Commissioner of Police in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Bala Ciroma has ordered an investigation into the death of one Blessing Otunla, who recent graduated from the University of Abuja. The deceased, who is suspected to have been raped before being killed, was found naked in a gutter at Student Village in Iddo Sarki, Abuja on Saturday. Findings revealed that Oyunla who travelled from Oyo to Abuja to collect her result, studied English Language at the university and graduated in 2020.  A statement issued yesterday by police spokesman  Yusuf Mariam  said: “The FCT Police Command condemns in totality the murder of one Blessing Otunla, a former student of the University of Abuja, whose body was found along Iddo Village axis and was killed by unknown assailants. “The Commissioner of Police Bala Ciroma has ordered full-scale investigation into the unfortunate incident and launched a manhunt for the perpetrators while commiserating with the family of the deceased.” “The Command implores residents to report all suspicious movements, emergency or distress”. 